cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DL 

This paper discusses the security of the TLS protocol and proposes a new notary service that leverages blockchain technology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of the proposed system, which falls under the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). The proposed system also involves network infrastructure, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of cs.DL (Machine Learning).
